    <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="T_Menu">Mechanism menu</text> combines commands from three toolbars:</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-ModelElements(Mechanism)" styleclass="VariableName">Model elements</link> &#160;- to add elements that arrange the layout of the machine.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Mechanism-Kinematic-Elements" styleclass="VariableName">Kinematic elements</link><text styleclass="VariableName"> - </text><text styleclass="Body Text">to add elements that represent</text> the moving parts in your machine. You join <text styleclass="Element-Header">Parts</text> to each other to form kinematic-<text styleclass="Body Text">chains (mechanisms, linkages).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Menu-Machine-Elements" styleclass="VariableName">Machine elements</link><text styleclass="Body Text"> &#160;- to add elements that represent the hardware components on industrial machines.</text></para>
